6.2 — New Section: Session Closure Declaration
Add a new sub-section within the evidence packet’s existing Section 5 (Current Session State) that explicitly declares the closure authority and reason:
## 5. Current Session State (As of Last Recorded Event)

- Session Status: TIMED_OUT
- Evidence Container: CLOSED
- Closure Event: EVT-0xx (SESSION_TIMEOUT)
- Closure Authority: SYSTEM (SYSTEM_TIMEOUT)
- Closure Reason: SYSTEM_TIMEOUT_MAX_DURATION
- Closure Timestamp: 10:47:42 UTC

### CLOSURE DECLARATION (mandatory):
This session was closed by automatic system enforcement upon reaching
the configured maximum session duration (48 hours, as set by the
facility). This closure:

  - Is NOT a CHECK_OUT event.
  - Does NOT indicate the driver or vehicle left the facility.
  - Does NOT indicate work was completed.
  - Does NOT make any determination about detention, delay, or liability.
  - Represents ONLY the closure of this evidentiary record container
    to maintain session discipline and evidentiary integrity.

If the driver remained on-site after this closure, that status is
reflected in a SEPARATE session with a distinct Session ID and
independent evidence packet.
6.3 — Cross-Session References (NOT Merging)
When an evidence packet’s session has related prior/subsequent sessions (e.g., FORCED_CLOSE_ON_OVERLAP referencing a new session, or CONTINUED_PRESENCE referencing a prior session), the evidence packet must include a ‘Related Sessions’ section:
## 10. Related Sessions (Non-Merging Cross-References)

The following sessions are chronologically adjacent to this one but are
INDEPENDENT evidence containers with their own Session IDs, hash chains,
and verifiable integrity. They are NOT merged with this session.

### Prior Session (if any)
- Session ID: S-EGW09-[prior]
- Relationship: This session begins after the prior session’s
  closure. Prior session was closed by: [SYSTEM_TIMEOUT / FORCED_CLOSE].
- Verification: [hash of prior session]

### Subsequent Session (if any)
- Session ID: S-EGW09-[next]
- Relationship: The subsequent session began after this session’s
  closure. Subsequent session reason: [CONTINUED_PRESENCE / NEW_CHECKIN].
- Verification: [hash of subsequent session]

### Notice
EvidenceLedger does NOT infer continuity between these sessions.
External parties evaluating time on-site across multiple sessions must
do so using the raw timestamps from each session’s authoritative events.

